  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the legitimate economy\n\nCommon legal elements include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origin of funds\n- Attempting to disguise illegal financial proceeds\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal income\n- Transferring money to avoid reporting requirements\n\nSpecific details and penalties differ by country, with most developed nations having robust anti-money laundering (AML) laws.",
